  "title": "A Furball and a Firebrand",
  "summary": "In the Cat's Claw cantina, the quarren pirate captain Salty Jack and his squib crewmate Grizz are playing sabacc when a candy-obsessed Ewok named Munch wanders in scrounging for food. Amused by the little creature -- who spears Grizz's fish and offers a charred lump of fallen metal as a gift -- Jack decides to adopt Munch into his crew. The boisterous Sharktooth Sally swaggers in with her own flask and, after tossing down what credits she has, talks her way onto the crew as well. Jack's one-eyed Mon Calamari first mate Barnacle Bill arrives with a datapad of dismal, barely-spaceworthy ship listings to replace their lost vessel, the Freedom Fish; he nearly comes to blows with Munch over a perceived insult about his missing eye before Jack restores order. The scene closes with the unlikely band -- quarren, squib, Ewok, Mon Calamari, and human firebrand -- assembled as a ragtag pirate crew bound for a grand adventure.",
